

@section Navbar{
    @await Html.PartialAsync("_navbarTSA.cshtml")
}

<link href="~/css/site.css" rel="stylesheet" />

<div class="container" style="align-self:center; justify-self:center; margin: 0px !important; padding:0px !important;">
    <h2 class="mb-5" style="align-content:center; justify-content:center; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;"><strong>
        Getting Started with Student Information System Admin Panel
    </strong></h2>
  
    <div id="carouselExample" class="carousel carousel-dark carousel-fade slide" data-bs-ride="carousel">
        <div class="carousel-indicators">
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="0" class="active noShadow" aria-current="true" aria-label="Slide 1"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="1" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 2"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="2" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 3"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="3" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 3"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="4" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 4"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="5" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 5"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="6" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 6"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="7" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 7"></button>
            <button type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide-to="8" class="noShadow" aria-label="Slide 8"></button>
        </div>
      <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="carousel-item active" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminOffcanvas.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminOffcanvas">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
          <h5>
              <b>
                  Ease of Use
              </b>
          </h5>

          <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
              The admin panel is designed in a simple and well-organized manner, so the admin can easily adapt to the panel.
          </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminAddNewTeacher.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminAddNewTeacher">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                      Teacher Registration
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0"  style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can efficiently add new teachers to the system. 
                  Since personnel entries are managed by administrators, the system becomes more secure.
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminAddNewStudent.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminAddNewStudent">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                    Student Registration
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can efficiently add new students to the system. 
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminStudentList.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminStudentList">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                    Student List
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can view all students registered in the system. 
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminStudentDetails.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminStudentDetails">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                    Student Details
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can view details of each of the student in the system. 
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminTeacherList.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminTeacherList">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                    Teacher List
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can view list of teachers in the system. Teachers lacking a reference letter 
                  and CV are shown on red cards. Unapproved teachers are shown on yellow cards and confirmed teachers
                  are shown on blue cards. This makes the system more manageable and understandable.
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminTeacherDetailsNoConfirmNoDoc.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminTeacherDetailsNoConfirmNoDoc">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                    Teacher Details Lacking Reference Letter and CV
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can view details of each teacher lacking a reference letter and CV in the system. 
                  Since the reference letter and CV do not exist in the system, administrators cannot approve the teacher. However,
                  the teacher can be terminated from the system.
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminTeacherDetailsConfirmTeacher.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminTeacherDetailsConfirmTeacher">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                    Unapproved Teacher Details
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can view details of each unapproved teacher in the system. 
                  When the CV and Reference Letter of a teacher are examined and approved by the administrators, 
                  the teacher will be able to create private lessons in the system.
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item" data-bs-interval="20000">
          <img src="/images/AdminGettingStarted/adminTeacherDetailsConfirmedTeacher.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="adminTeacherDetailsConfirmedTeacher">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block mb-5">
              <h5>
                  <b>
                    Confirmed Teacher Details
                  </b>
              </h5>
              <p class="mb-0" style="margin-left: 18px;margin-right: 18px;">
                  Administrators can view details of each confirmed teacher in the system.  
              </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button class="carousel-control-prev carousel-fade" type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" 
      data-bs-slide="prev">
        <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
      </button>
      <button class="carousel-control-next carousel-fade" type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExample" data-bs-slide="next">
        <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
      </button>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-5" style="align-content:center; justify-content:center; 
    margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto; text-indent:30px;font-size:larger;">
        Student Information System (SIS) is an application designed to connect private teachers and students in a safe environment.
        The system creates a student pool for private teachers and a private teacher pool for students. However, 
        the system offers more than just a pool. Since the system is managed by administrators, any issues arising on the student side
        or teacher side can be solved efficiently by the administrators. This makes the system more secure and reliable. 
        <br /> <br />As a result, responsibilities of the administrators can be summarized as follows:
        <ul style="font-size:larger;margin-left:0px;padding-left:15px;list-style:none;">
            <li class="mb-2 adminGS">
                 Adding new teachers to the SIS,
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2 adminGS">
                 Adding new students to the SIS,
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2 adminGS">
                 Confirming teachers, 
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2 adminGS">
                 Terminating teachers,
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2 adminGS">
                 Terminating students,
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2 adminGS">
                 Resolving issues between teachers and students.
            </li>
        </ul>

    </p>
</div>
